**Input Validation**
- SQL injection vulnerabilities (raw queries, unsanitized inputs)
- XSS vulnerabilities in frontend (dangerouslySetInnerHTML, unsanitized user content)
- Path traversal in file operations
- Command injection in shell executions

**Secrets & Configuration**
- Hardcoded credentials, API keys, passwords
- Secrets committed to git (check .gitignore)
- Environment variables properly used
- Debug mode disabled for production

**API Security**
- CORS configuration (overly permissive origins)
- Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints
- Proper HTTP methods (no GET for mutations)
- Error messages leaking sensitive info

**Data Protection**
- Password hashing (bcrypt, not MD5/SHA1)
- Sensitive data in logs
- PII exposure in API responses
- Database cascade deletes configured

